{"heading":"Aaron makes a golden calf, which Israel worships—Moses serves as a mediator between God and rebellious Israel—Moses breaks the tablets of stone—The Levites slay about 3,000 rebels—Moses pleads and intercedes for the people.","number":32,"verseCount":35,"verses":[[1,["And when the people saw that Moses ",["delayed",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 24:18","ot/ex/24.18"],"; ",["34:28","ot/ex/34.28"],"; ",["Deut. 9:9","ot/deut/9.9"],"."]]]," to come down out of the mount, the people gathered themselves together unto Aaron, and said unto him, Up, make us ",["gods",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 32:23","ot/ex/32.23"],"; ",["Acts 7:40","nt/acts/7.40"],"."]]],", which shall ",["go",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 13:21","ot/ex/13.21"],"."]]]," before us; for ",["as for",["clarity-word"]]," ",["",130],"this Moses, the man that brought us up out of the land of Egypt, we ",["wot",["study-note-ref","d",["OR know (also ",["v. 23","ot/ex/32.23"],")."]]]," not what is become of him."]],[2,["And Aaron said unto them, Break off the ",["golden",["study-note-ref","a",[["Judg. 8:26 (24–27)","ot/judg/8.26"],"."]]]," earrings, which ",["are",["clarity-word"]]," in the ears of your wives, of your sons, and of your daughters, and bring ",["them",["clarity-word"]]," unto me."]],[3,["And all the people brake off the golden earrings which ",["were",["clarity-word"]]," in their ears, and brought ",["them",["clarity-word"]]," unto Aaron."]],[4,["And he received ",["them",["clarity-word"]]," at their hand, and fashioned it with a graving tool, after he had made it a ",["molten",["study-note-ref","a",[["Neh. 9:18","ot/neh/9.18"],"; ",["Ps. 106:19","ot/ps/106.19"],"; ",["D&C 124:84","dc-testament/dc/124.84"],"."]]]," calf: and they said, ",["These",["study-note-ref","b",[["Alma 30:53","bofm/alma/30.53"],"."]]]," ",["be",["clarity-word"]]," thy ",["gods",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 20:23","ot/ex/20.23"],"; ",["Acts 7:41","nt/acts/7.41"],"; ",["Rom. 1:23 (18–25)","nt/rom/1.23"],". ",["TG Idolatry","tg/idolatry"],"."]]],", O Israel, which brought thee up out of the land of Egypt."]],[5,["And when Aaron saw ",["it,",["clarity-word"]]," he built an altar before it; and Aaron made proclamation, and said, To morrow ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," a feast to the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],"."]],[6,["And they rose up early on the morrow, and offered burnt offerings, and brought ",["peace offerings",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 24:5 (5–8)","ot/ex/24.5"],"."]]],"; and the ",["people",["study-note-ref","b",[["1 Cor. 10:7","nt/1-cor/10.7"],"."]]]," sat down to eat and to drink, and rose up to play."]],[7,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," said unto Moses, Go, get thee down; for thy people, which thou broughtest out of the land of Egypt, have ",["corrupted",["study-note-ref","a",[["Gen. 6:11 (11–13)","ot/gen/6.11"],"; ",["Deut. 4:16 (14–19)","ot/deut/4.16"],"; ",["9:12 (11–15)","ot/deut/9.12"],"; ",["Hosea 9:9 (7–9)","ot/hosea/9.9"],"; ",["D&C 38:11","dc-testament/dc/38.11"],"."]]]," ",["themselves:",["clarity-word"]]]],[8,["They have ",["turned",["study-note-ref","a",[["Deut. 9:16","ot/deut/9.16"],"; ",["1 Ne. 17:30 (30–31, 42)","bofm/1-ne/17.30"],"; ",["D&C 84:24 (23–25)","dc-testament/dc/84.24"],"."]]]," aside ",["quickly",["study-note-ref","b",[["Alma 46:8","bofm/alma/46.8"],"; ",["Hel. 12:4 (2–7)","bofm/hel/12.4"],"."]]]," out of the way which I commanded them: they have made them a ",["molten",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 20:4 (3–4, 23)","ot/ex/20.4"],"."]]]," calf, and have worshipped it, and have sacrificed thereunto, and said, These ",["be",["clarity-word"]]," thy gods, O Israel, which have brought thee up out of the land of Egypt."]],[9,["And the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," said unto Moses, I have seen this people, and, behold, it ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," a ",["stiffnecked",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Apostasy of Israel","tg/apostasy-of-israel"],"; ",["Stiffnecked","tg/stiffnecked"],"."]]]," people:"]],[10,["Now therefore let me alone, that my ",["wrath",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 22:24","ot/ex/22.24"],"; ",["D&C 84:24","dc-testament/dc/84.24"],"."]]]," may wax hot against them, and that I may ",["consume",["study-note-ref","b",[["Deut. 9:14 (13–14)","ot/deut/9.14"],", ",["19 (18–20)","ot/deut/9.19"],"; ",["Ps. 106:23","ot/ps/106.23"],"."]]]," them: and I will make of thee a great ",["nation",["study-note-ref","c",[["Num. 14:12","ot/num/14.12"],"."]]],"."]],[11,["And Moses ",["besought",["study-note-ref","a",[["Deut. 9:18 (18, 26–29)","ot/deut/9.18"],"."]]]," the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," his God, and said, ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", why doth thy wrath wax hot against thy people, which thou hast brought forth out of the land of Egypt with great power, and with a mighty hand?"]],[12,["Wherefore should the ",["Egyptians",["study-note-ref","a",[["Num. 14:13 (13–16)","ot/num/14.13"],"; ",["Deut. 9:28","ot/deut/9.28"],"."]]]," speak, and say, For mischief did he bring them out, to slay them in the mountains, and to consume them from the face of the earth? Turn from thy fierce ",["wrath",["study-note-ref","b",["JST Ex. 32:12 … wrath. Thy people will repent of this evil; therefore come thou not out against them."]]],", and ",["repent",["study-note-ref","c",[["Gen. 6:6","ot/gen/6.6"],"; ",["Ex. 32:14","ot/ex/32.14"],"; ",["Deut. 9:19","ot/deut/9.19"],"."]]]," of this evil against thy people."]],[13,["Remember ",["Abraham",["study-note-ref","a",[["2 Kgs. 13:23","ot/2-kgs/13.23"],"."]]],", Isaac, and Israel, thy servants, to whom thou ",["swarest",["study-note-ref","b",[["Gen. 22:16 (15–19)","ot/gen/22.16"],"."]]]," by thine own self, and saidst unto them, I will ",["multiply",["study-note-ref","c",[["D&C 27:10","dc-testament/dc/27.10"],"; ",["Abr. 1:2","pgp/abr/1.2"],"."]]]," your ",["seed",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Seed of Abraham","tg/seed-of-abraham"],"."]]]," as the stars of heaven, and all this ",["land",["study-note-ref","e",[["TG Promised Lands","tg/promised-lands"],"."]]]," that I have spoken of will I give unto your seed, and they shall inherit ",["it",["clarity-word"]]," for ever."]],[14,[["And",["study-note-ref","a",[["JST Ex. 32:14 (Appendix)","jst/jst-ex/32.14"],"."]]]," the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," ",["repented",["study-note-ref","b",[["Gen. 6:6","ot/gen/6.6"],"; ",["Ex. 32:12","ot/ex/32.12"],"; ",["Num. 23:19","ot/num/23.19"],"."]]]," of the evil which he thought to do unto his people."]],[15,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And Moses turned, and went down from the mount, and the two ",["tables",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 24:12","ot/ex/24.12"],"; ",["34:29","ot/ex/34.29"],"; ",["Deut. 4:13","ot/deut/4.13"],"."]]]," of the testimony ",["were",["clarity-word"]]," in his hand: the tables ",["were",["clarity-word"]]," written on both their sides; on the one side and on the other ",["were",["clarity-word"]]," they written."]],[16,["And the ",["tables",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Law of Moses","tg/law-of-moses"],"."]]]," ",["were",["clarity-word"]]," the work of God, and the ",["writing",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Scriptures, Writing of","tg/scriptures-writing-of"],"."]]]," ",["was",["clarity-word"]]," the ",["",131],"writing of God, graven upon the tables."]],[17,["And when ",["Joshua",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 17:9","ot/ex/17.9"],"; ",["24:13","ot/ex/24.13"],"; ",["33:11","ot/ex/33.11"],"."]]]," heard the noise of the people as they ",["shouted",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Rioting and Reveling","tg/rioting-and-reveling"],"."]]],", he said unto Moses, ",["There is",["clarity-word"]]," a noise of war in the camp."]],[18,["And he said, ",["It is",["clarity-word"]]," not the voice of ",["them that",["clarity-word"]]," ",["shout for mastery",["study-note-ref","a",["HEB call for courage."]]],", neither ",["is it",["clarity-word"]]," the voice of ",["them that",["clarity-word"]]," cry for being overcome: ",["but",["clarity-word"]]," the noise of ",["them that",["clarity-word"]]," sing do I hear."]],[19,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And it came to pass, as soon as he came nigh unto the camp, that he ",["saw",["study-note-ref","a",[["Deut. 9:16 (16–17, 21)","ot/deut/9.16"],"."]]]," the calf, and the dancing: and Moses’ ",["anger",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Anger","tg/anger"],"."]]]," waxed hot, and he cast the tables out of his hands, and ",["brake",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 34:1","ot/ex/34.1"],"; ",["D&C 84:23 (19–26)","dc-testament/dc/84.23"],"."]]]," them beneath the mount."]],[20,["And he took the ",["calf",["study-note-ref","a",[["Deut. 9:21","ot/deut/9.21"],"."]]]," which they had made, and burnt ",["it",["clarity-word"]]," in the fire, and ground ",["it",["clarity-word"]]," to powder, and ",["strawed",["study-note-ref","b",["OR strewed."]]]," ",["it",["clarity-word"]]," upon the ",["water",["study-note-ref","c",[["Deut. 9:21","ot/deut/9.21"],"."]]],", and made the children of Israel drink ",["of it.",["clarity-word"]]]],[21,["And Moses said unto Aaron, What did this people unto thee, that thou hast brought so great a sin upon them?"]],[22,["And Aaron said, Let not the ",["anger",["study-note-ref","a",[["Gen. 44:18","ot/gen/44.18"],"; ",["Deut. 9:20","ot/deut/9.20"],"."]]]," of my lord wax hot: thou knowest the people, that they ",["are ",["set",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 16:20 (19–21)","ot/ex/16.20"],"."]]],["clarity-word"]]," on ",["mischief",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 14:11","ot/ex/14.11"],"; ",["17:2 (2, 4)","ot/ex/17.2"],"."]]],"."]],[23,["For they said unto me, ",["Make",["study-note-ref","a",[["Acts 7:40","nt/acts/7.40"],"; ",["1 Ne. 17:42","bofm/1-ne/17.42"],"."]]]," us ",["gods",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 32:1","ot/ex/32.1"],"."]]],", which shall go before us: for ",["as for",["clarity-word"]]," this Moses, the man that brought us up out of the land of Egypt, we wot not what is become of him."]],[24,["And I said unto them, Whosoever hath any gold, let them break ",["it",["clarity-word"]]," off. So they gave ",["it",["clarity-word"]]," me: then I cast it into the fire, and there came out this calf."]],[25,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And when Moses saw that the people ",["were",["clarity-word"]]," ",["naked",["study-note-ref","a",["OR riotous, let loose."]]],"; (for Aaron had made them ",["naked",["study-note-ref","b",[["2 Chr. 28:19","ot/2-chr/28.19"],"; ",["2 Ne. 9:14","bofm/2-ne/9.14"],"; ",["Morm. 9:5","bofm/morm/9.5"],"."]]]," unto ",["their",["clarity-word"]]," shame among their enemies:)"]],[26,["Then Moses stood in the gate of the camp, and said, Who ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," on the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],"’s side? ",["let him come",["clarity-word"]]," unto me. And all the sons of Levi gathered themselves together unto him."]],[27,["And he said unto them, Thus saith the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," God of Israel, Put every man his sword by his side, ",["and",["clarity-word"]]," go in and out from gate to gate throughout the camp, and ",["slay",["study-note-ref","a",[["Num. 25:5","ot/num/25.5"],"."]]]," every man his brother, and every man his companion, and every man his neighbour."]],[28,["And the children of Levi did according to the word of Moses: and there fell of the people that day about three thousand men."]],[29,["For Moses had said, ",["Consecrate",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Dedication","tg/dedication"],"."]]]," yourselves to day to the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", even every man upon his ",["son",["study-note-ref","b",[["Deut. 13:6 (6–11)","ot/deut/13.6"],"."]]],", and upon his brother; that he may bestow upon you a ",["blessing",["study-note-ref","c",[["D&C 130:20","dc-testament/dc/130.20"],"; ",["132:5","dc-testament/dc/132.5"],"."]]]," this day."]],[30,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And it came to pass on the morrow, that Moses said unto the people, Ye have ",["sinned",["study-note-ref","a",[["1 Sam. 12:20 (20–25)","ot/1-sam/12.20"],"."]]]," a great sin: and now I will go up unto the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],"; ",["peradventure",["study-note-ref","b",["OR perhaps."]]]," I shall make an ",["atonement",["study-note-ref","c",[["Num. 25:13","ot/num/25.13"],"."]]]," for your sin."]],[31,["And Moses returned unto the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]],", and said, Oh, this people have sinned a great sin, and have made them ",["gods",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Worship","tg/worship"],"."]]]," of gold."]],[32,["Yet now, if thou wilt ",["forgive",["study-note-ref","a",[["Deut. 9:26 (18, 26–29)","ot/deut/9.26"],"."]]]," their sin—; and if not, ",["blot",["study-note-ref","b",[["Rom. 9:3","nt/rom/9.3"],"."]]]," me, I pray thee, out of thy ",["book",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ps. 139:16","ot/ps/139.16"],"."]]]," which thou hast ",["written",["study-note-ref","d",[["Luke 10:20","nt/luke/10.20"],"."]]],"."]],[33,["And the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," said unto Moses, ",["Whosoever",["study-note-ref","a",[["A of F 1:2","pgp/a-of-f/1.2"],"."]]]," hath ",["sinned",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Accountability","tg/accountability"],"."]]]," against me, him will I ",["blot out",["study-note-ref","c",[["Mosiah 26:36","bofm/mosiah/26.36"],"; ",["Alma 1:24","bofm/alma/1.24"],"; ",["6:3","bofm/alma/6.3"],"; ",["Moro. 6:7","bofm/moro/6.7"],"; ",["D&C 20:83","dc-testament/dc/20.83"],"."]]]," of my ",["book",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Book of Life","tg/book-of-life"],"; ",["Book of Remembrance","tg/book-of-remembrance"],"; ",["Record Keeping","tg/record-keeping"],"."]]],"."]],[34,["Therefore now go, ",["lead",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 33:12","ot/ex/33.12"],"."]]]," the people unto ",["the place",["clarity-word"]]," of which I have spoken unto thee: behold, mine ",["Angel",["study-note-ref","b",[["Num. 20:16","ot/num/20.16"],"."]]]," shall go before thee: nevertheless in the day when I visit I will visit their sin upon them."]],[35,["And the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," plagued the people, because they made the calf, which Aaron made."]]],"volume":"ot"}